Ecosystem & Tooling Selection
  Before writing code, we need to map the Python libraries to their C++ equivalents and set up the build system.


   * Build System: CMake (Industry standard for C++).
   * Computer Vision: OpenCV C++ (cv::VideoCapture, cv::Mat).
   * Inference (YOLOv11): TensorRT (NVIDIA) or ONNXRuntime. We will need to export your .pt models to .onnx or .engine formats.
   * Object Tracking: C++ implementation of ByteTrack (readily available on GitHub).
   * Messaging (RabbitMQ): amqp-cpp or SimpleAmqpClient.
   * Web Streaming (MJPEG): cpp-httplib (lightweight header-only HTTP server).
   * Motor Control (Moteus): Moteus provides a C++ API (moteus-cpp or direct SocketCAN wrappers).
   * Hardware/Serial Comm: Boost.Asio or a lightweight library like serialib for Arduino (Trigger, Sensors, Zoom).
   * Configuration/State: nlohmann/json for JSON parsing (for runtime_state.json, fov_data.json, etc.).